<p>&nbsp;</p></div><div class="onMount-appear-done onMount-enter-done" style="margin-top: 20px;"><h2 class="componentsMainHeading fs20">FAQs</h2><div style="margin-top: 10px;"><div class="cur-po faq567QuesBorder"><div class="valign-wrapper vspace-between "><h3 class="ac11Title fw400 faq567Ques fs16 ">What sort of loans can I use the EMI calculator for?</h3><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" height="20" width="20" class="ac11Icon absolute-center  ac11collapsibleClose"><path d="M0 0h24v24H0V0z" fill="none"></path><path d="M7.41 8.59L12 13.17l4.59-4.58L18 10l-6 6-6-6 1.41-1.41z"></path></svg></div><div class="ac11Hidden" style="height: 0px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 100%;"><div><div class="faq567Ans fs16 "><div class="faq567HtmlContent"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You can use this online EMI calculator for all types of loans including personal loans, business loans, and car loans. All you need to know is the interest rate payable on the principal amount and the tenure.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="cur-po faq567QuesBorder"><div class="valign-wrapper vspace-between "><h3 class="ac11Title fw400 faq567Ques fs16 ">How does the debt-to-income ratio affect my chances of availing of a loan?</h3><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" height="20" width="20" class="ac11Icon absolute-center  ac11collapsibleClose"><path d="M0 0h24v24H0V0z" fill="none"></path><path d="M7.41 8.59L12 13.17l4.59-4.58L18 10l-6 6-6-6 1.41-1.41z"></path></svg></div><div class="ac11Hidden" style="height: 0px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 100%;"><div><div class="faq567Ans fs16 "><div class="faq567HtmlContent"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">To avail of a loan, your debt-to-income ratio should not be more than 50%. Otherwise, the lending institution will be led to believe that you may not have the wherewithal to repay the loan.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="cur-po faq567QuesBorder"><div class="valign-wrapper vspace-between "><h3 class="ac11Title fw400 faq567Ques fs16 ">What does an EMI consist of?</h3><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" height="20" width="20" class="ac11Icon absolute-center  ac11collapsibleClose"><path d="M0 0h24v24H0V0z" fill="none"></path><path d="M7.41 8.59L12 13.17l4.59-4.58L18 10l-6 6-6-6 1.41-1.41z"></path></svg></div><div class="ac11Hidden" style="height: 0px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 100%;"><div><div class="faq567Ans fs16 "><div class="faq567HtmlContent"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">An Equated Monthly Instalment represents a part of your principal amount and interest payable. It has to be paid until the tenure ends. Alternatively, you can settle the debt with a one-time payment.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="cur-po faq567QuesBorder"><div class="valign-wrapper vspace-between "><h3 class="ac11Title fw400 faq567Ques fs16 ">What happens if I fail to pay my EMIs?</h3><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" height="20" width="20" class="ac11Icon absolute-center  ac11collapsibleClose"><path d="M0 0h24v24H0V0z" fill="none"></path><path d="M7.41 8.59L12 13.17l4.59-4.58L18 10l-6 6-6-6 1.41-1.41z"></path></svg></div><div class="ac11Hidden" style="height: 0px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 100%;"><div><div class="faq567Ans fs16 "><div class="faq567HtmlContent"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Financial institutions levy heavy penalties on unpaid EMIs. If you miss an EMI, you may have to pay extra in the future.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="cp46RightSide"><div class="scc87MainDiv center-align"><div class="lazyload-wrapper "><img class="" src="//assets-netstorage.groww.in/web-assets/billion_groww_desktop/prod/_next/static/media/defaultSidebar.b40891fd.svg" width="130" height="87" alt="sidebar cta image" loading="lazy"></div><d