022-04-11T11:16:37.000Z","updatedAt":"2023-05-10T11:22:59.200Z","calculator_widget":"EMI Calculator","faqs":[{"id":2764,"question":"What sort of loans can I use the EMI calculator for?","answer":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eYou can use this online EMI calculator for all types of loans including personal loans, business loans, and car loans. All you need to know is the interest rate payable on the principal amount and the tenure.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"},{"id":2765,"question":"How does the debt-to-income ratio affect my chances of availing of a loan?","answer":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eTo avail of a loan, your debt-to-income ratio should not be more than 50%. Otherwise, the lending institution will be led to believe that you may not have the wherewithal to repay the loan.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"},{"id":2766,"question":"What does an EMI consist of?","answer":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eAn Equated Monthly Instalment represents a part of your principal amount and interest payable. It has to be paid until the tenure ends. Alternatively, you can settle the debt with a one-time payment.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"},{"id":2767,"question":"What happens if I fail to pay my EMIs?","answer":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eFinancial institutions levy heavy penalties on unpaid EMIs. If you miss an EMI, you may have to pay extra in the future.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"}]}}},"page":"/calculators/[searchId]","query":{"searchId":"emi-calculator"},"buildId":"JqJohdJs_yPQe_am0yorh","assetPrefix":"//assets-netstorage.groww.in/web-assets/billion_groww_desktop/prod","isFallback":false,"dynamicIds":[44930],"gip":true,"scriptLoader":[{"nonce":"vPrHjksqBnijt+rd4ZwdFQFWg6ECZWf+5EFpZn9GgkE=","strategy":"afterInteractive","id":"_webengage_script_tag","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":" var webengage;!function(w,e,b,n,g){function o(e,t){e[t[t.length-1]]